              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "197Au target with thickness of 0.25 mg/cm2 was used"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " At one side of the beam an fixed array of four",
                "Si detectors positioned at 73, 78, 83, and 89 deg was",
                "used. On the other side of the beam there were two",
                "independently movable arrays, one at forward angles",
                "and one at backward angles. The forward array",
                "consisted of three detectors nominally separated in",
                "angle by 5deg. The backward array consisted of seven",
                "detectors nominally separated by 5deg from each other.",
                "All the array detectors had an area of 300 mm2 and",
                "were positioned at approx. 320 mm from the target"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The beam was bunched into packets with a FWHM of 0.71",
                "ns. The average time between beam bursts was 82 ns."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " From the particle time of flight and energy,",
                "the mass of the fragment was calculated.",
                "All beam energies are center of target beam energies",
                "calculated using code SRIM"
              ]
            }
          ],
